On 6/14/03 2:52 PM, "Eric W. Bradway" <eric(-at-)bradway.net> wrote:

> I've got my front wheel hub in the oven in an attempt to get the bearing races
> out. Any idea how long and how hot?
> 
> It's at 350 F now and has been about 15 minutes. I've taken it out twice and
> tried to drift them out to no avail...

I don't know about removal since both parts are going to expand with the
heat. Using the oven is an installation trick: you freeze the races at the
same time you heat the hub then remove both and put the races in quickly.

